content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Unlisted music tracks
For shorter unlisted music fragments, see Jingles.

Unlisted music tracks are, as opposed to regular music tracks, not listed in the Music Player and as such can only be heard a limited amount of times, usually once.

They are usually played during quest cutscenes or in certain areas instead of background music. These unlisted tracks have no official name, and the music player appears as if the game is silent. They are less abundant than normal music tracks, and the known ones are listed here:

Old School RuneScape music player

Unlisted tracks[edit | edit source]

These tracks are classified as music tracks that play instead of default music. The music player will display a blank track name, and the track will play repeatedly if music looping is enabled.

Track Release Played while
Church Music 1 Before June 2004 Playing a church organ.
Church Music 2 Before June 2004 Playing a church organ.
Massacre 6 June 2016 Previously played during the World 666 event in June 2016.
Preserved-vation 7 September 2017 A remix of Preservation and Preserved that plays during Bone Voyage.

Cutscene tracks[edit | edit source]

These tracks are classified as music tracks that play on top of default music. They will only play once, and the music player will display the name of the previous track that was playing.

Track Released Location
Cannon fodder 21 March 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Between a Rock..., when Dondakan launches the player from the multicannon into Dondakan's mine.
The Face of a King 31 May 2005 Plays during the cutscene in The Giant Dwarf, when the rebuilt statue of King Alvis is revealed. It is based upon Land of the Dwarves.
Wise Old Theme (short) 6 June 2005 A shorter version of the Wise Old Man's theme, this track plays during:
  • The encounter with the Thing under the bed
  • A cutscene during Making Friends with My Arm, where the Wise Young Man drives back the trolls of Weiss from Keldagrim.

It is based upon Scape Main.

Magic Carpet ride 5 July 2005 Plays when travelling via the Magic Carpet.
Forgettable Intro... 26 July 2005 Plays during the title cutscene of Forgettable Tale... It is based upon Right on Track.
Forgettable Meeting... 26 July 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Forgettable Tale..., when the Red Axe's plans are revealed. It is based upon Right on Track.
Forgettable Drunk... 26 July 2005 Plays during the ending cutscene in Forgettable Tale..., when the player tells stories of kebabs. It is a remix of Tale of Keldagrim.
Billy and Bob 30 August 2005 Plays during Garden of Tranquillity, in the cutscene showing Billy and Bob.
Touring the Garden 30 August 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Garden of Tranquillity, when King Roald tours the completed garden.
Meet Captain Braindeath 31 October 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Rum Deal, when the player is first taken to Braindeath Island and meets Captain Braindeath. It is a remix of Blistering Barnacles.
Zombie Pirates 31 October 2005 This jingle plays:
  • During a cutscene in Rum Deal, where Captain Braindeath shows the horde of Zombie protesters outside their brewery.
  • When inspecting Hans' chart during the 20th Anniversary event.
  • During the first cutscene of the 2021 Birthday event.

It is based upon Blistering Barnacles.

Denath, Meet Evil Dave 14 November 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Shadow of the Storm, when entering the Uzer throne room with Evil Dave. It is based upon Throne of the Demon.
Outpost Cutscene 22 November 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Making History showing the history of the Outpost. It is based upon Neverland.
Pied Piper 28 November 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Ratcatchers, when all the rats in Port Sarim are lured into the sea.
A Devious Assassin Appears 19 December 2005 Plays during the cutscene in Devious Minds, when the Relic is stolen from Entrana. It is based upon Background.
Bert's Lovely Sand 10 January 2006 Plays during the cutscene in The Hand in the Sand, when Bert's sandpit is enchanted to have infinite sand. It is based upon Big Chords.
Enakhra's Lament 1 23 January 2006 Plays during the first flashback cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when Enakhra completes the temple. It is based upon Lament.
Enakhra's Lament 2 23 January 2006 Plays during the second flashback cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when Enakhra creates weapons for Zamorak. It is based upon Lament.
Enakhra's Lament 3 23 January 2006 Plays during the third flashback cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when the Avarrockians attempt to stop Enakhra. It is based upon Lament.
Enakhra's Lament 4 23 January 2006 Plays during the fourth flashback cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when Enakhra joins Akthanakos. It is based upon Lament.
Enakhra's Lament 5 23 January 2006 Plays during the fifth flashback cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when Enakhra betrays Akthanakos. It is based upon Lament.
Enakhra's Lament 6 23 January 2006 Plays during the final cutscene of Enakhra's Lament, when Akthanakos is freed by the player. It is based upon Lament.
The "Death" of Juliet 7 March 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Romeo & Juliet, when Juliet drinks the Cadava potion. It is based upon Spirit.
Romeo mourns 7 March 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Romeo & Juliet, when Romeo enters the crypt looking for Juliet. It is based upon Garden.
The Secret Banquet 15 March 2006 Plays during Recipe for Disaster, in the cutscene of the Secret Council's banquet.
Hawaii 5-Ogre 15 March 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Recipe for Disaster, when Bugs and Fycie's Ogre boat first arrived.
The Guests are Free! 15 March 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Recipe for Disaster, after saving the final member of the Secret Council.
Gadderanks suspense 22 March 2006 Plays during the cutscence in In Aid of the Myreque, before the player fights Gadderanks. It is based upon Distant Land.
Tolna leaves home 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when Tolna leaves home. It is based upon No Way Out.
Theme of Anger 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when first entering the Anger room. It is based upon No Way Out.
Theme of Confusion 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when first entering the Confusion room. It is based upon No Way Out.
Theme of Fear 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when first entering the Fear room. It is based upon No Way Out.
Theme of Hopelessness 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when first entering the Hopelessness room. It is based upon No Way Out.
Tolna the Abomination 3 April 2006 Plays during the cutscene in A Soul's Bane, when entering the final room with Tolna. It is based upon No Way Out.
Wise Old Theme 2 May 2006 Plays during a cutscene in Swan Song, in which Herman Caranos describes the past adventures of the Wise Old Man. It is based upon Scape Main.
A Royal Plan 22 May 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Royal Trouble, when Prince Brand and Princess Astrid explain their plan to prevent war between Miscellania and Etceteria. It is based upon Land Down Under.
Ambient Church Happy 31 May 2006 Plays when using the Church organ in a Player-owned house.
Zanik's Resurrection 21 June 2006 Plays during a cutscene in Death to the Dorgeshuun, when Zanik is revived by the Tears of Guthix. It is based upon Tears of Guthix
Sigmund's Plan 21 June 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Death to the Dorgeshuun, when Zanik recalls Sigmund's evil plan. It is based upon H.A.M. Fisted.
Mizgog's Beads 4 July 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Imp Catcher, when all the beads are returned to Mizgog. It is based upon Vision.
Lunar Isle entrance 24 July 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Lunar Diplomacy, when the player first enters the Moon Clan village. It is based upon The Lunar Isle.
The Potion is Ruined 7 August 2006 Plays during the cutscene in Black Knight's Fortress, when Lensig's potion is ruined. It is based upon Alone.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Battlefield 1 15 August 2006 Plays during the battlefield cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the gnome and goblin armies face off. It is based upon Attack 1.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Battlefield 2 15 August 2006 Plays during the battlefield cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Glouphrie summons an illusionary army of tortoises. It is based upon Attack 1.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Battlefield 3 15 August 2006 Plays during the battlefield cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the goblin army retreats. It is based upon Attack 1.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Spirit Tree 1 15 August 2006 Plays during the spirit tree cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie, depicting Argento and his death.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Spirit Tree 2 15 August 2006 Plays during the spirit tree cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Argento is shown to have died, marking the end of the cutscene.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 1 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when King Healthorg and Glouphrie are summoned to Argento's location. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 2 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Oaknock and Hazelmere breaks Glouphrie's illusion to reveal that Argento was long dead. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 3 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when King Healthorg asks Glouphrie to explain himself. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 4 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Glouphrie tells King Healthorg that some things are best kept secret, even from his king ("Occasionally.") It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 5 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when King Healthorg tells Glouphrie that he is no longer his advisor and to leave the Stronghold. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 6 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Glouphrie tells King Healthorg that his empire will crack without someone like himself. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion 7 15 August 2006 Plays during the expulsion cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when Glouphrie walks away from the king, to mark the end of the cutscene. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Sabotage 1 15 August 2006 Plays during the sabotage cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the saboteur enters Brimstail's cave while the player is talking to Brimstail. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Sabotage 2 15 August 2006 Plays during the sabotage cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the player and Brimstail walk back to the main room, marking the end of the cutscene. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Izzie transforms 1 15 August 2006 Plays during the transformation cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the player returns to Brimstail after fixing Oaknock's machine. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Izzie transforms 2 15 August 2006 Plays during the transformation cutscene in The Eyes of Glouphrie, when the cute creature is revealed to be an evil creature, and marks the end of the cutscene. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Spotted by Vanstrom! 4 September 2006 Plays during Darkness of Hallowvale, when the player is spotted by Vanstrom Klause outside Castle Drakan. It is based upon Fangs for the Memory.
The Slug Brother Maledict 20 September 2006 Plays during a cutscene in The Slug Menace, when Brother Maledict becomes possessed by the sea slugs. It is based upon The Mollusc Menace.
The Slug Prince 20 September 2006 Plays during a cutscene in The Slug Menace, when the Slug Prince appears. It is based upon Slug a Bug Ball.
The Slug Queen, Mother Mallum 20 September 2006 Plays during a cutscene in The Slug Menace, when Mother Mallum appears. It is based upon Slug a Bug Ball.
Cooking an Adventurer 23 October 2006 This jingle plays during:
  • A cutscene in My Arm's Big Adventure, when Burntmeat is cooking the adventurer
  • Cutscenes in Making Friends with My Arm, where My Arm first meets Larry, and when he enters Weiss.

It is a remix of Marzipan.

Rumble in da jungle 23 October 2006 Plays during a cutscene in My Arm's Big Adventure, during My Arm's rampage in Tai Bwo Wannai. It is based upon Marzipan.
Chicken Grab 12 December 2006 Plays during a cutscene in Animal Magnetism, when Alice's husband is chasing the sneaky undead fowl.
Meet Tarn Razorlor 22 January 2007 Plays during the miniquest Lair of Tarn Razorlor, when meeting Tarn for the first time.
Meet Tarn Razorlor 2 22 January 2007 Plays during the miniquest Lair of Tarn Razorlor, when Tarn transforms into a mutant form.
Slice of Grand Opening 24 April 2007 Plays during the cutscene in Another Slice of H.A.M., showing the grand opening of the Dorgesh-Kaan–Keldagrim train system.
Witch's Gramophone (fixed) 4 June 2007 Plays when players kick the gramophone in Nora T. Hagg's house. The track initially keeps jumping when wound up, and is kicked to play this version of the track.
Witch's Gramophone (broken) 4 June 2007 Plays when players wind-up the gramophone in Nora T. Hagg's house. The track will keep jumping until the gramophone is kicked, which will then play the proper version of the track.
Witch's Piano Demo 4 June 2007 Plays when pressing the "Demo" button on right side of the piano in the basement of Nora T. Hagg's house.
Christmas Tree (2014) 18 December 2014 Played during the cutscene in 2014 Christmas event when the Varrock tree was fully decorated. It is based upon Diango's Little Helpers.
My Arm meets Snowflake 6 September 2018 Plays during a cutscene in Making Friends with My Arm, when My Arm meets Snowflake for the first time. It is a remix of Snowflake & My Arm.
My Arm marries Snowflake 6 September 2018 Plays during a cutscene in Making Friends with My Arm, after pronouncing My Arm and Snowflake as husband and wife. It is a remix of Snowflake & My Arm.

Unused[edit | edit source]

These tracks are not used anywhere in-game, but exist as files in the game's code.

Track Added to cache Location
Game Intro 1 Before June 2004 Presumably the original title screen music that was replaced by Scape Original. Voyage was possibly a reworked version of the track. It was removed on 26 September 2019.
Ambience 2 Before June 2004 Presumably composed for the music update in 2004. It was removed on 26 September 2019.
Ambience 3 Before June 2004 Presumably composed for the music update in 2004. It was removed on 26 September 2019.
Ambience 4 Before June 2004 Presumably composed for the music update in 2004. Overture was possibly a reworked version of the track. It was removed on 26 September 2019.
Fade Test Before June 2004 An extended version of Ambience 4, presumably composed for the music update in 2004. Overture was possibly a reworked version of the track. It was removed on 26 September 2019.
The Adventurer 11 April 2005 An unreleased version of the music added in the Tutorial Update in 2008. It was possibly intended to be new title screen music.
Petra Fiyed Freed 28 February 2005 Presumably intended to play during One Small Favour when Petra Fiyed is freed. It is based upon Goblin Game.
Ambient Church Moody N/A Added in 2005, it was presumably intended to play on a church organ.
Ambient Church Spooky N/A Added in 2005, it was presumably intended to play on a church organ.
Drunken Dwarf 26 July 2005 Presumably intended for a cutscene during Forgettable Tale... It is a remix of Land of the Dwarves.
Athlete's Foot 9 August 2005 Intended to play during the scrapped Speedy Gnome random event.
Autumn in Bridgelum Unknown A remix of Autumn Voyage, it was intended to play during the scrapped Duke of Bridgelum random event.
Garden of Tranquillity - unused 30 August 2005 A more cheerful version of Billy and Bob's theme that was presumably intended to play during Garden of Tranquillity, although the track appears unfinished and ends abruptly halfway through.
Mined Out Unknown Added sometime between August or September 2005. It is not known what the track was intended for.
Royal Trouble - Cutscene 1 extended 22 May 2006 An extended version of the cutscene music played during Royal Trouble. It is based upon Land Down Under.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Battlefield Theme 15 August 2006 The main theme of the tracks played in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie that depicts the Battle of Atarisundri. It is based upon Attack 1.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Expulsion Theme 15 August 2006 The main theme of the tracks played in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie that depicts Glouphrie's expulsion. It is based upon Long Ago.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Izzie's Tranformation Theme 15 August 2006 The main theme of the tracks played in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie that depicts the reveal of the cute creature's true appearance. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Sabotage Theme 15 August 2006 The main theme of the tracks played in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie that depicts the saboteur's sabotage. It is based upon Brimstail's Scales.
Eyes of Glouphrie - Spirit Tree Theme 15 August 2006 The main theme of the tracks played in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie that depicts Argento's death.
Seaslug Sailing Journey 20 September 2006 An unreleased version of the Sailing theme that was intended to play during The Slug Menace. It was removed on 26 September 2019. It is based upon Scape Original.
Spy Games Unknown Added sometime between 22nd and 28th March 2006, it was possibly intended to play during Contact!, or Osman's scrapped subquest during Recipe for Disaster.

'''Unlisted music tracks''' are, as opposed to regular [[Music|music tracks]], not listed in the [[Music Player]] and as such can only be heard a limited amount of times, usually once.

They are usually played during [[quest]] [[cutscene]]s or in certain areas instead of background music. These unlisted tracks have no official name, and the music player appears as if the game is silent. They are less abundant than normal music tracks, and the known ones are listed here:
